description:
The original Fantastic Four are dead, and a New Fantastic Four has taken their place! But what can the team of Iron Man, Hulk, Spider-Man and Wolverine do against a foe as powerful as Thanos---bearer of the Infinity Gauntlet?

When it takes all the power of Iron Man's amazing new armor, all of Spider-Man's attitude, all the Hulk's brute strength, and all of Wolverine's underhanded tricks just to survive...what can the New Fantastic Four do to win? The answer lies within this cosmically power-packed issue!

Featuring Part 3 of "What If the Runaways became the Young Avengers?"
name: New Fantastic Four; The Mini Marvels Present... World War Hulk: Final Showdown; What if the Runaways Became the Toung Avengers, Part 3

description:
Cover date: September 1984

Cover Details - "Gee, Archie ! I Wonder If The Day Will Brighten Up !?

Archie Andrews & Jughead Jones as lifeguards at the beach observing two hot girls (one of whom resembles Cheryl Blossom but is not credited as such by the Grand Comics Database).

5 page Archie story "Strange Change"

Archie proves there is such a thing as a personality change.

6 page Marvelous Maureen story "Episode 18: Marvelous Maureen Makes A Transfer Or A Dud Plan"

Maureen & Mortimer trick the Grossniks and escape in a Raider ship.

4 page Big Moose story "Mammoth Madness"

After Moose falls out of a tree and bangs his head; he gets a visit from the gang who think he's gone crazy.

1 page Coach Kleats activity "Coach Kleats Sports Toss-Up !"

A Coach Kleats sports related word game.

6 page Archie story "Pool Party"

Archie & Jughead use Veronica's swimming pool and mistake Mr. Lodge for a thief.

source: Grand Comics Database (GCD)
